Name: Delta Analog Output Module (DVP04DA-S)
Short description:
• Brands Delta
  • Product Model: DVP04DA-S
  • Stock status: Out Of Stock
Description:
The Delta DVP04DA-S is a kind of Analog Output Module that is manufactured by Delta Electric. The origin of the Delta Analog Output Module DVP04DA-S is from China. The Delta Analog output Module DVP04DA-S is 4 channel PLC Analog Output Interface Module that is used in Industrial Automation and process control.

The Delta Analog Output Module DVP04DA-S is used in Delta Programmable Logic Controller. The Delta PLC is used in the industry and factory for the purpose of controlling machines, run machines, etc. Mainly the Delta PLC checks the monitor and produced output based on their custom program. That custom program is given to the Delta PLC.

In the Industrial Automation, many control signals are analog signals. The most frequently obtained range for the voltage signals is 0 ~ 10V and current signals are 0 ~ 20mA. For controlling the peripheral devices, the data in the PLC need to be converted into analog signals. The data in the Delta Analog Output Module DVP04DA-S can be read/written by using FROM/TO instructions in the program of DVP-PLC MPU. In this module, there are 49 16-bit control registers. The Delta Analog Output Module DVP04DA-S receives 12-bit digital data of 4 groups from PLC MPU. And that converts it into 4 points analog output signal, maybe it voltage or current.

The software version of the Delta Analog Output Module DVP04DA-S can be updated via RS-485 communication. The power unit and module are separate in this Delta Analog Output Module DVP04DA-S. The size is small so that it is easy to install. The user can select output from voltage or current via USB wiring. The voltage output range is almost 0V ~ +10VDC and the current output range is 0mA ~ 20mA. The power supply of this Delta Analog Output Module is 24V DC. In this Delta Analog Output Module the isolation between the digital area and analog area. But there is no isolation on the channel.

The voltage output of this Delta Analog Output Module DVP04DA-S has short circuit protection.

Description:
Description of this Product

\n

Panasonic PLC CPU AFPX-C14Tis a Programmable Logic Controller (PLC) which is manufactured by Panasonic. The Panasonic PLC CPU AFPX PLC Series succeeded the popular FP1. With these similar dimensions, higher processing speed increased memory capacity and optimized motion control signals. The AFPX is well suited for a wide variety of applications. The CPU is available with 14, 30, 38, and 60 I/Os and 32K steps program memory. There is a lot of communications slot for RS-232, RS-422, RS-485 and Ethernet communications. There is also a function slot for analog I/Os, RTD, thermocouple, pulse I/O, etc. These communication ports make AFPX even more flexible, enabling users to configure the controllers to match their application’s needs. There is no need for additional space for communication slots or cassettes, the user needs to plug them into the CPU. When there is need more functionality or I /Os, AFPX and FPOR expansion units can be connected.

A wide range of expansion modules allows to set up an individual LOGO! configuration.

LOGO! 8: 24 digital inputs, 20 digital outputs, 8 analog inputs and 8 analog outputs!

If you do networking of several LOGO! one configuration can be expanded to overall 88 digital inputs, 80 digital outputs, 40 analog inputs and 24 analog outputs. LOGO! 8 can also be connected to KNX sytems.

To combine different voltage levels you have to keep the following rule: The basic module must be a 230 V version followed by 230 V expansion modules. Then an analog module must be used to achieve a galvanic isolation. Right from the analog module further analog modules or 12V / 24 V expansions can be attached.

Siemens LOGO! 6 Series brings you additional features aimed at keeping the LOGO! At the forefront of this technology. The new generation LOGO! 0BA6 features yet another decisive advantage, the possibility to connect an extra text display without communication module. Proven to be a highly convenient for the projecting and display of operator relevant messages. The text display has been precisely optimized to the needs of a logic module and can be projected with the same function block as the internal display. Moreover, the performance of the basis module now enhanced by more than 50 percent to 200 function blocks. Thus, even more applications can be replaced through more cost-effective LOGO! Configurations, and savings potential can be tapped, Major improvements over previous LOGO! Units include:

  • LOGO! TD device directly connectable to all 0BA6 basic modules. • Display with adjustable permanent backlight (on-board and/or TD). • Up to 50 message text blocks (on-board and/or TD). • New integrated PWM functions. • Simple bar-graph functionality. • Text-ticker functionality. • 4 Analogue inputs (0-10V) - instead of 2. • 4 (5 kHz) fast counter-inputs - instead of 2 (2 kHz). • Analogue output 0 mA to 20 mA or 4 mA to 20 mA. • Ten different on-board languages (GE, EN, FR, IT, ES, CHN, JAP, TR, RUS, and NL).

Introduction to S7-200 Accessory Module EM221 8DI, 24 VDC

It is a thing which works as a micro-programmable logic controller used to control a huge kind of devices to run the automation world smoothly. It basically looks up and monitors the input system and changes outputs according to the need of a customer. This S7-200 Accessory Module EM221 8DI, 24 VDC besides controlling any program, it also operates Boolean logic, counting, timing, complex math operations and communication system to a great extent.

The S7-200 Accessory Module provides a user-friendly and contented atmosphere to procreate, control and monitor any logic to create a complete program. It is in a simple word, a small CPU for the normal automation task as it is the perfect small device for having a cost-effective programming solution. To expand the temperature range it can also be used. This is very beneficial for small but complex work, more complex machines and small systems solutions with component compact packages. In EM 221 8DI, PLC module is 24VDC 16 DI compatible Siemens s7-200 accessory.

This S7-200 accessory module EM221 8DI, 24VDC is fully compatible with s7-200 and s7-300 series programmable logic controller, STEP 7 software like MICRO/WIN where programming can be used directly by enhancing encryption algorithm for S7-200. EM series PLCs are high qualified, user-friendly and fully compatible with CPU, and the other device.

In the automation world, things become so easy and easy handled by using these devices, it is not only making everything easy but also give a cost-effective solution for the accessories. S7 200 accessory module is a product family of the SIMATIC  200 series.

In it, the product type designation is BU type A0, HW functional status states from FS06. It supplies voltage in 24 V rated voltage (DC). It is 24 V DC/A miniature circuit breaker with type B or C tripping characteristics for an external protection power supply line.

It has no mains filter. For P1 and P2 bus, max current carrying capacity is 10 A, and for process terminals maximum current carrying capacity is 2 A.  In the term of hardware configuration, it has an automatic coding system, but it has no formation of potential groups. In it, potential the group continued from the left.

In the S7-200 accessory module, Its isolation tested with 707 V DC. It has many Ambient temperatures during operation. In the horizontal installation, min is -30 degrees Celsius and a maximum of 60 degrees Celsius. On the other hand, in the vertical installation, min is 30 degrees Celsius and the maximum is 50 degrees Celsius. Installation altitude above sea level maximum is 2000 m; on request installation altitude is greater than 2000 m. For process terminals, color coding labels are CC00 to CC09, for AUX and add on terminals it does not exist.

Description:
Siemens S7-222 CPU

14 on board I/O 4kbytes programme memory 2kbytes data memory 4 x 30kHz high speed counter Real time clock option, see stock no. 488-6381

Note

Output ratings are 28.8Vdc maximum for transistor outputs (stock no. 488-6381, 30Vdc or 240Vac maximum for relay outputs 488-6381.

Siemens S7-200 Base Units - 3rd Generation

The S7 brings to the user a powerful solution to a host of control applications, which is easy to adapt and expand the system. The S7 is a family of PLCs which allows the user to tailor their selection of components which best suits their requirements, and is the long term successor to the highly successful S5 range. Whatever the S5 can do, the S7 can do more quickly and more easily. The 3rd generation of S7-200 now builds on the success of the original range and exploits new CPU's in order to produce even faster and more powerful range of PLC's. The range of CPU's available has been increased with the introduction of the new 224XP, as has the range of digital, analogue and communications expansion modules. For the faster type of application real time control is easily achieved by use of the comprehensive range of built-in interrupts. Timed, Communication, High Speed Counter, High Speed Pulse Output, and hardware interrupts are all available, and the implementation of a priority table means that all the interrupts can work simultaneously. Communications with S7-200 is built in. Inter PLC communications is achieved using two wire network which can be up to 1200 meters and can have up to 126 nodes. In "Freeport" mode the PLC's RS-485 port runs in free ASC11 mode making it possible to communicate with other devices. In line with Siemens objective to make the programming of S7-200 as user friendly as possible MicroWin programming software has been further improved. These improvements all help minimise program development time. This has been achieved by including more and improving existing "wizards". These help program developers with the more routine/complex parts of their programs, e.g. TD200 configuration, PID loop configuration, High Speed Counter configuration, etc. Inclusion of context sensitive help also means that all the information required is at the users fingertips.

New CPU hardware support provides the option to turn off run mode edit to obtain more program memory CPU 224XP supports onboard analogue I/O and two communication ports CPU 226 includes additional input filters and pulse catch facility 0.22μs processing time per instruction

Modular Expansion up to 256 total I/O (except S7-221) Powerful Instruction Set, and Real Time performance Programming via RS-485 comms port All models have EEPROM memories for user program storage 2 or 4 x 30kHz pulse train outputs (dc powered models only )

Description:
Siemens S7-200 PLC Analog Output Module (6ES7232-0HD22-0XA0)

The S7 brings to the user a powerful solution to a host of control applications, which is easy to adapt and expand the system. The S7 is a family of PLC’s which allows the user to tailor their selection of components which best suits their requirements, and is the long term successor to the highly successful S5 range. Whatever the S5 can do, the S7 can do more quickly and more easily.,The 3rd generation of S7-200 now builds on the success of the original range and exploits new CPU’s in order to produce even faster and more powerful range of PLC's. The range of CPU's available has been increased with the introduction of the new 224XP, as has the range of digital, analogue and communications expansion modules.,For the faster type of application real time control is easily achieved by use of the comprehensive range of built-in interrupts. Timed, Communication, High Speed Counter, High Speed Pulse Output, and hardware interrupts are all available, and the implementation of a priority table means that all the interrupts can work simultaneously.,Communications with S7-200 is built in. Inter PLC communications is achieved using two wire network which can be up to 1200 meters and can have up to 126 nodes. In "Freeport" mode the PLC's RS-485 port runs in free ASC11 mode making it possible to communicate with other devices.,In line with Siemens objective to make the programming of S7-200 as user friendly as possible MicroWin programming software has been further improved. These improvements all help minimise program development time. This has been achieved by including more and improving existing "wizards". These help program developers with the more routine/complex parts of their programs, e.g. TD200 configuration, PID loop configuration, High Speed Counter configuration, etc. Inclusion of context sensitive help also means that all the information required is at the users fingertips. New CPU hardware support provides the option to turn off run mode edit to obtain more program memoryCPU 224XP supports onboard analogue I/O and two communication portsCPU 226 includes additional input filters and pulse catch facility0.22μs processing time per instruction Modular Expansion up to 256 total I/O (except S7-221)Powerful Instruction Set, and Real Time performanceProgramming via RS-485 comms portAll models have EEPROM memories for user program storage2 or 4 x 30kHz pulse train outputs (dc powered models only )

Name: Variable Frequency Inverter,3.7/5.5kw, 440v
Description:
Variable Frequency Inverter,3.7/5.5kw,440v

If your small rating variable frequency drive (VFD) getting damage then there may be a voltage spikes issue because according to the thumb rule if the transformer KVA rating is 10 times of KVA rating of VFD, say a 100 kVA transformer for 10 hp VFD, then it is subjected to voltage spikes that can damage it. Line reactors are the best way to compensate for that but most users don't use the reactors for small rating VFDs.

If your VFD is large enough compared to your generator then there can be issues with the semi-conductors on the VFD firing correctly. This was an issue one of the VFDs experts always checked when large VFDs needed to be run by a back-up generator.

You may always want to look at the power quality during start-up. A voltage spike will damage the semiconductors on the front end to the VFD. So if you were using the reactors then the problem may be different but if you don't then I suggest you use reactors.

Name: Variable Frequency Inverter, 7.5/11kw, 440V, 3-Phase
Description:
Description of this Product:

In the industrial automation in the sector, there is a need for variable Frequency Inverter, 7.5/11kW, 440V, 3-Phase to control the speed of the motor. The Variable Frequency Inverter, 7.5/kW, 440V, 3-Phase change the speed of a motor by changing some parameters. These parameters are frequency and supplied voltage to the used motor. By changing the frequency and supply voltage of a motor, the Variable Frequency Inverter, 7.5/11kW, 440v, 3-Phase can run the motor slowly or speedy.

Consider, power supplied to an AC The motor is 50 Hz, then the motor will run at its rated speed. If the frequency increases by about more than 50 Hz, the motor will run faster than its rated speed. If the frequency reduces to 50 Hz, the motor will run slower than at its rated speed.

The Variable Frequency Inverter, 7.5/11kW, 440V, 3-Phase is not much expensive to use in industry or factory. This Variable Frequency Inverter is a high-frequency variable drive. There is a communication port, that is RS485 enabled. The Variable Frequency Inverter consists of the Input/Output module, where are rated current, input voltage, input frequency, output voltage, output frequency, and overload capacity.

Control Panel:

The Variable Frequency Inverter, 7.5/11kW, 440V, 3-Phase has a control feature. This control panel consists of control mode, communication port, speed regulation, starting torque, speed control accuracy, frequency precision, frequency resolution, torque boost, interior PID controller, automatic energy save running, automatic voltage regulation, and automatic current limiting, etc.

Siemens S7-1500, digital output module DQ 8x230 V AC/2 A ST; TRIAC; 8 channels in groups of 1; 2 A per group; Substitute value: Front connector (screw terminals or push-in) to be ordered separately

Digital output modules switch 24 V DC or 230 V AC voltages in the plant and thus transfer internal signals from the controller to the plant. Solenoid valves, DC contactors, and indicator lights can be connected.

35 mm wide output modules have settable parameters and diagnostic functions and can thus be adapted flexibly to the respective process requirements.

25 mm wide output modules do not have settable parameters or diagnostic functions and can therefore be integrated very easily into the engineering. They are recommended for use in locations where only very few input channels are necessary or under conditions of use in which a high number of channels must be implemented in a very limited space.

Both module types can be used side by side in one station as required. Uniform features and shared system accessories guarantee easy handling.

The following digital output modules with a width of 35 mm are available:

DQ 16x24VDC/0.5A ST; digital output module with 16 channels 24 V DC / 0.5 A (transistor); two potential groups; 4 A per group; parameterizable diagnostics; parameterizable substitute value for the outputs

DQ 32x24VDC/0.5A ST; digital output module with 32 channels 24 V DC / 0.5 A (transistor); four potential groups; 4 A per group; parameterizable diagnostics; parameterizable substitute value for the outputs

DQ 8x24VDC/2A HF; digital output module with 8 channels 24 V DC / 2 A (transistor); one potential group; 8 A per group; parameterizable diagnostics; parameterizable substitute value for the outputs; option of using two channels for pulse width modulation (PWM) up to 500 Hz

DQ 8x230VAC/2A ST (triac); digital output module with eight outputs 230 V AC / 2 A (triac); 8 potential groups; 2 A per group; parameterizable substitute value for the outputs

DQ 8x230VAC/5A ST (relay); digital output module with eight outputs 230 V AC / 5 A (relay); 8 potential groups; 5 A per group; parameterizable substitute value for the outputs

DQ 16x230VAC/1A ST (triac); digital output module with 16 outputs 230 V AC / 1 A (triac); 8 potential groups; 2 A per group; parameterizable substitute value for the outputs

DQ 16x230VAC/2A ST (relay); digital output module with 16 outputs 230 V AC / 2 A (relay); 8 potential groups; 4 A per group; parameterizable substitute value for the outputs

DQ 16x24V…48VUC/125VDC/0.5A ST; digital output module with 16 outputs 24…24 V UC bus 125 V DC / 0.5 A; 16 potential groups; 0.5 A per group; parameterizable substitute value for the outputs

The following digital output modules with a width of 25 mm are available:

DQ 16x24VDC/0.5A BA; digital output module with 16 channels 24 V DC / 0.5 A (transistor); sourcing output; two potential groups; 4 A per group

DQ 32x24VDC/0.5A BA; digital output module with 16 channels 24 V DC / 0.5 A (transistor); sourcing; four potential groups; 4 A per group

The SIMATIC S7-1500 and ET 200MP system addresses applications and market segments with high and extremely high performance requirements. The complete system performance is optimized for this purpose. In the case of the SIMATIC ET 200MP this optimization already begins with the I/O modules. For example: there are digital input modules with minimum filtering times and analog modules with conversion times down to 62.5µs (AI) and 125µs (AO) for 8 channels. For quick transport of the data the ET 200MP makes use of a backplane bus that is approx. 40-times faster than the backplane bus of today's S7-400 PLC. In addition, SIMATIC ET 200MP consistently uses innovative and proven PROFINET mechanisms, so that already at the time of delivery release bus cycle times of down to 250µs are possible. These can be coupled to the isochronous task of the CPU (Isochronous mode). The new S7-1500 CPUs with their optimized commands and compilers ensure fast data processing and thus enable shortest possible response times to also serve applications with maximum performance requirements. It goes without saying that the system was designed such, that suitable system reserves are available to guarantee long-term investment protection.

Description:
Descriptions of this Product:

The Delta Inverter VFD004M21A is manufactured by Delta and is from China. The Delta Inverter is the vast number of users in the industry/factory for the purpose of controlling the speed of the motor. Its compact-sized design makes more reliable and ideal for small and medium-sized applications. The Delta Inverter VFD004M21A is a sensorless vector AC Drive. This Delta Inverter VFD004M21A designed to offers ultra low noise operations. In industrial automation, there is use a lot of machines, and need Delta Inverter to control the speed of a motor. And this inverter also protects the motor from any unexpected co-incidence. To protect the motors, the Delta Inverter VFD004M21A includes several kinds of innovative technologies so that it can reduce or deduct any kind of interference.

The Delta Inverter VFD004M21A for AC motors have been the new invention that has brought the AC motors in its original characteristics. The Delta Inverter VFD004M21A can vary the speed of a motor by changing the frequency of the voltage which has been used to power it. That means if the voltage applied to an AC motor which is 50Hz then the motor will run or works at its rated speed. If the frequency increase about more than 50Hz, then the motor, will run or works faster than the rated speed. If the frequency is less than the 50Hz, the motor will work slower than the rated speed.

According to the VariableFrequency Driver (VFD), the Delta Inverter VFD004M21A is an electronic device that is designed to change or vary the frequency of the voltage supplied to the AC induction motor.
